pkg — package manager

SYNOPSIS
  pkg list
  pkg info ID
  pkg install [-f] (DIR | ID)
  pkg uninstall ID
  pkg verify ID

DESCRIPTION
  Manages OCOS packages. A package is a directory tree with
  manifest.cfg declaring id / version / depends / caps_required and a
  files table with sha256 per file. Local installs (DIR) read from a
  directory; remote installs (ID) resolve through the registries
  configured in /etc/registries.cfg.

  The local package database lives at /var/db/pkg/. install records
  every file's expected sha256 there; verify re-hashes them later.
  -f forces install over an existing version of the same id.

EXAMPLES
  pkg list                           installed packages
  pkg install ./hello/               from a local directory
  pkg install com.example.editor     from a configured registry
  pkg verify com.example.editor      re-check the file hashes
  pkg uninstall com.example.editor

SEE ALSO
  registries(5)
